\label{eq:reducedAMEs}

text:
\begin{align}
\dot{\rho} &= h(\nu, t) - \rho, \\
\dot{\nu} &= g(\nu, t) - \nu,
\end{align}

prevtext:
\end{subequations}
with the quantities $g(\nu)$ and $h(\nu)$ given explicitly by Eqs.~(\ref{eq:gFactor}) and~(\ref{eq:hFactor}).

The system~(\ref{eq:reducedAMEs}) can be solved numerically to obtain $\rho(t)$ and thus characterize the temporal evolution of the adoption process. Let us further separate the fraction of adopters as $\rho(t) = \rho_0(t) + \rho_1(t)$, where $\rho_0$ and $\rho_1$ are the fractions of innovators and induced adopters (i.e. vulnerable and stable nodes), respectively. Now consider the identity,

